# Okta Security Policies Configuration

## Project Overview

This lab documents the configuration of security policies in Okta for the TechMigos environment. The goal was to control user access based on network location, session lifetime, MFA requirements, and authenticator enrollment.

---

## Objectives

- Create network zones for trusted and untrusted access.
- Configure Global Session Policy rules.
- Require MFA based on network risk.
- Configure authenticator enrollment policies.
- Apply stronger security controls to high-risk groups.
- Document policy behavior for GitHub portfolio review.

---

## 1. Network Zones Configuration

Network zones were created to classify traffic based on trusted and untrusted locations.

### Configured Network Zones

| Zone Name | Zone Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Trusted-Corporate | IP Zone | Represents trusted company network access |
| Untrusted-Network | IP Zone | Represents risky or unknown network access |
| Corporate-VPN | IP Zone | Represents VPN-based company access |
| Restricted Network | Dynamic Zone | Blocks or limits access from restricted countries |
| Trusted Network (GH) | Dynamic Zone | Allows trusted access from Ghana location |

