## 2. Global Session Policy

A custom Global Session Policy was created to manage Okta session behavior for the **TechMigos CyberOps** group.

### Policy Name

**Company Access Policy**

### Assigned Group

**TechMigos CyberOps**

### Policy Purpose

This policy controls how users authenticate into Okta and how long their session remains active.

---

## 3. Global Session Policy Rules

Two rules were configured under the Company Access Policy.

---

### Rule 1: Trusted Network Access

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Rule Name | Trusted Network |
| Location | In zone: Trusted-Corporate |
| Access | Allowed |
| MFA | Required |
| MFA Prompt | Every sign-in |
| Maximum Okta Global Session Lifetime | 8 hours |
| Session Lifetime | 2 hours |
| Persistent Browser Session | Disabled |

### Purpose

This rule allows users from the trusted corporate network to access Okta with MFA. The session time is longer because the user is coming from a trusted location.

### Screenshot

![Trusted Network Rule](../docs/images/trusted-network-rule.png)

---

### Rule 2: Untrusted Network Access

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Rule Name | Untrusted Network |
| Location | In zone: Untrusted-Network |
| Access | Allowed |
| MFA | Required |
| MFA Prompt | Every sign-in |
| Maximum Okta Global Session Lifetime | 4 hours |
| Session Lifetime | 15 minutes |
| Persistent Browser Session | Disabled |

### Purpose

This rule applies stricter session controls when users sign in from an untrusted network. Even though access is allowed, the session lifetime is shorter to reduce risk.

